I"q<p>The aim is to find more accessible and robust solutions for the patterns we author, plug in, and use every day.</p>

<p>Each chapter tackles a single component, addressing how different and vulnerable people might read and interact with it, and how they can be better accommodated. The in-depth explorations are meticulously illustrated and code examples culminate as working demos.</p>

<p>Inclusive design is not about wrong and right, but <em>bad to better</em>. You’ll learn plenty of tips from <strong>Inclusive Components</strong>, but you’ll also adopt the mindset to go on and make even better components.</p>
